AWARD-WINNING rapper Blxckie almost started the year on the wrong foot. The artist, who shot to fame over the past few years, almost died in a car accident on his way to a gig on New Year’s Eve. Blxckie, whose real name is Sihle Sithole, said he was travelling from Lesotho to Joburg with his team to catch a flight to Durban when their car got a puncture and crashed into the side of the road. The 22-year-old said the bad luck didn’t stop there, as the car got a second puncture on arrival in Joburg. “I’ve never been in such a hectic accident, but luckily we all survived,” he said. ALSO READ | UNATHI LEAVES SOCIAL MEDIA DROOLING His publicity manager Kim Sineke said the rapper was doing well and grateful to be alive. “Although the driver lost control of the car and it ended up on the side of the road, he did an amazing job in ensuring everyone was safe and unharmed. “Blxckie is grateful he did not suffer any injuries as it could have been worse,” she said. Kim said although he was left shaken, Blxckie didn’t cancel his gigs and was continuing with his tour. “Even though he said the accident was hectic and he had never experienced something like that before, he’s continuing with his work. He’s deeply sorry for not making it to the events he was booked for, but it was beyond his control,” she said.